at is very familiar with amateurs is the famous stick figure (as said before these drawings should be quick and spontaneous, a common error among amateurs is working for too long on one gesture drawing such as a &quot;stick figure&quot;). Gesture Drawings can be compared to the finess of handling a blade in fencing. With such grace a gesture drawing should be done, atleast that's what my Art teacher says. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=durakken>Durakken</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(8/21/03 9:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12664.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re:</span><hr size=1> Honestly...just about everything i've ever posted on this bored is a doodle for me...granted a doodle isn't supposed to take an hour or so...but in my oppinion if you are just playing and are not using your full skill level it's a doodle...and because of this in my oppinion many pieces that are great could be considered doodles...even if they take 8 to 20 hours. Some people play..while other actually work and try to do stuff... <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showPrevMessage?topicID=12664.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showNextMessage?topicID=12664.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12664.topic&index=9><img src=http://www.polykarbon.com/bbsimage/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0>